48 template <typename Impl>
49 class TileReference {
50  private:
51  template <typename, typename>
52  friend class ArrayIterator;
53 
54  template <typename>
55  friend class TileConstReference;
56 
57  typedef typename Impl::range_type range_type;
58  typedef typename Impl::range_type::index index_type;
59  typedef typename Impl::size_type ordinal_type;
60 
61  Impl* tensor_;
62  ordinal_type index_;
63 
64  // Not allowed
65  TileReference<Impl>& operator=(const TileReference<Impl>&);
66 
67  public:
68  TileReference(Impl* tensor, const typename Impl::size_type index)
69  : tensor_(tensor), index_(index) {}
70 
71  TileReference(const TileReference<Impl>& other)
72  : tensor_(other.tensor_), index_(other.index_) {}
73 
74  template <typename Value>
75  TileReference<Impl>& operator=(const Value& value) {
76  tensor_->set(index_, value);
77  return *this;
78  }
79 
80  typename Impl::future future() const {
81  TA_ASSERT(tensor_);
82  return tensor_->get(index_);
83  }
84 
85  typename Impl::value_type get() const {
86  // NOTE: return by value to avoid lifetime issues.
87  TA_ASSERT(tensor_);
88  return future().get();
89  }
90 
91  operator typename Impl::future() const { return this->future(); }
92 
93  operator typename Impl::value_type() const { return get(); }
94 
96 
98  index_type index() const {
99  TA_ASSERT(tensor_);
100  return tensor_->tiles_range().idx(index_);
101  }
102 
104 
106  ordinal_type ordinal() const { return index_; }
107 
109 
111  range_type make_range() const {
112  TA_ASSERT(tensor_);
113  return tensor_->trange().make_tile_range(index_);
114  }
115 
116 }; // class TileReference

132 std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, const TileReference<Impl>& a) {

135 }

234 template <typename Impl, typename Reference>
235 class ArrayIterator {
236  private:
237  // Give access to other iterator types.
238  template <typename, typename>
239  friend class ArrayIterator;
240 
241  Impl* array_;
242  typename Impl::pmap_interface::const_iterator it_;
243 
244  public:
245  typedef ptrdiff_t difference_type;
246  typedef
247  typename Impl::future value_type;
248  typedef PointerProxy<value_type> pointer;
249  typedef Reference reference;
250  typedef std::forward_iterator_tag
251  iterator_category;
252  typedef ArrayIterator<Impl, Reference> ArrayIterator_;
253  typedef typename Impl::range_type::index index_type;
254  typedef typename Impl::size_type ordinal_type;
255  typedef typename Impl::range_type range_type;
256  typedef typename Impl::value_type tile_type;
257 
258  private:
259  void advance() {
260  TA_ASSERT(array_);
261  const typename Impl::pmap_interface::const_iterator end =
262  array_->pmap()->end();
263  do {
264  ++it_;
265  } while ((it_ != end) && array_->is_zero(*it_));
266  }
267 
268  public:
270  ArrayIterator() : array_(NULL), it_() {}
271 
273  ArrayIterator(Impl* tensor, typename Impl::pmap_interface::const_iterator it)
274  : array_(tensor), it_(it) {}
275 
277 
279  ArrayIterator(const ArrayIterator_& other)
280  : array_(other.array_), it_(other.it_) {}
281 
283 
286  template <
287  typename I, typename R,
288  typename std::enable_if<!((!std::is_const<Impl>::value) &&
289  std::is_const<I>::value)>::type* = nullptr>
290  ArrayIterator(const ArrayIterator<I, R>& other)
291  : array_(other.array_), it_(other.it_) {}
292 
294 
297  ArrayIterator_& operator=(const ArrayIterator_& other) {
298  array_ = other.array_;
299  it_ = other.it_;
300 
301  return *this;
302  }
303 
305 
309  template <typename R>
310  ArrayIterator_& operator=(const ArrayIterator<Impl, R>& other) {
311  array_ = other.array_;
312  it_ = other.it_;
313 
314  return *this;
315  }
316 
318 
320  ArrayIterator_& operator++() {
321  advance();
322  return *this;
323  }
324 
326 
328  ArrayIterator_ operator++(int) {
329  ArrayIterator_ tmp(*this);
330  advance();
331  return tmp;
332  }
333 
335 
340  template <typename I, typename R>
341  bool operator==(const ArrayIterator<I, R>& other) const {
342  return (array_ == other.array_) && (it_ == other.it_);
343  }
344 
346 
351  template <typename I, typename R>
352  bool operator!=(const ArrayIterator<I, R>& other) const {
353  return (array_ != other.array_) || (it_ != other.it_);
354  }
355 
357 
359  reference operator*() const {
360  TA_ASSERT(array_);
361  return reference(array_, *it_);
362  }
363 
365 
367  pointer operator->() const {
368  TA_ASSERT(array_);
369  return pointer(array_->get(*it_));
370  }
371 
373 
375  index_type index() const {
376  TA_ASSERT(array_);
377  return array_->tiles_range().idx(*it_);
378  }
379 
381 
383  ordinal_type ordinal() const {
384  TA_ASSERT(array_);
385  return *it_;
386  }
387 
389 
391  range_type make_range() const {
392  TA_ASSERT(array_);
393  TA_ASSERT(it_ != array_->pmap()->end());
394  return array_->trange().make_tile_range(*it_);
395  }
396 
397 }; // class TensorIterator

408 template <typename Tile, typename Policy>
409 class ArrayImpl : public TensorImpl<Policy> {
410  public:
411  typedef ArrayImpl<Tile, Policy> ArrayImpl_;
412  typedef TensorImpl<Policy> TensorImpl_;
413  typedef typename TensorImpl_::size_type size_type;
414  typedef typename TensorImpl_::policy_type
415  policy_type;
416  typedef typename TensorImpl_::trange_type
417  trange_type;
418  typedef typename TensorImpl_::range_type
419  range_type;
420  typedef typename TensorImpl_::shape_type shape_type;
421  typedef typename TensorImpl_::pmap_interface
422  pmap_interface;
423  typedef Tile value_type;
424  typedef
425  typename eval_trait<Tile>::type eval_type;
426  typedef typename numeric_type<value_type>::type
427  numeric_type;
428  typedef DistributedStorage<value_type>
429  storage_type;
430  typedef typename storage_type::future future;
431  typedef TileReference<ArrayImpl_> reference;
432  typedef TileConstReference<ArrayImpl_>
433  const_reference;
434  typedef ArrayIterator<ArrayImpl_, reference> iterator;
435  typedef ArrayIterator<const ArrayImpl_, const_reference>
436  const_iterator;
437 
438  private:
439  storage_type data_;
440 
441  public:
443 
451  ArrayImpl(World& world, const trange_type& trange, const shape_type& shape,
452  const std::shared_ptr<pmap_interface>& pmap)
453  : TensorImpl_(world, trange, shape, pmap),
454  data_(world, trange.tiles_range().volume(), pmap) {}
455 
457  virtual ~ArrayImpl() {}
458 
460 
465  template <typename Index>
466  future get(const Index& i) const {
467  TA_ASSERT(!TensorImpl_::is_zero(i));
468  return data_.get(TensorImpl_::trange().tiles_range().ordinal(i));
469  }
470 
472 
477  template <typename Integer>
478  future get(const std::initializer_list<Integer>& i) const {
479  return get<std::initializer_list<Integer>>(i);
480  }
481 
483 
491  template <typename Index, typename Value>
492  void set(const Index& i, const Value& value) {
493  TA_ASSERT(!TensorImpl_::is_zero(i));
494  const auto ord = TensorImpl_::trange().tiles_range().ordinal(i);
495  data_.set(ord, value);
496  if (set_notifier_accessor()) {
497  set_notifier_accessor()(*this, ord);
498  }
499  }
500 
502 
504  iterator begin() {
505  // Get the pmap iterator
506  typename pmap_interface::const_iterator it = TensorImpl_::pmap()->begin();
507 
508  // Find the first non-zero iterator
509  const typename pmap_interface::const_iterator end =
510  TensorImpl_::pmap()->end();
511  while ((it != end) && TensorImpl_::is_zero(*it)) ++it;
512 
513  // Construct and return the iterator
514  return iterator(this, it);
515  }
516 
518 
520  const_iterator cbegin() const {
521  // Get the pmap iterator
522  typename pmap_interface::const_iterator it = TensorImpl_::pmap()->begin();
523 
524  // Find the fist non-zero iterator
525  const typename pmap_interface::const_iterator end =
526  TensorImpl_::pmap()->end();
527  while ((it != end) && TensorImpl_::is_zero(*it)) ++it;
528 
529  // Construct and return the iterator
530  return const_iterator(this, it);
531  }
532 
534 
536  iterator end() { return iterator(this, TensorImpl_::pmap()->end()); }
537 
539 
541  const_iterator cend() const {
542  return const_iterator(this, TensorImpl_::pmap()->end());
543  }
544 
546 
548  const madness::uniqueidT& id() const { return data_.id(); }
549 
550  static std::function<void(const ArrayImpl_&, int64_t)>&
551  set_notifier_accessor() {
552  static std::function<void(const ArrayImpl_&, int64_t)> value;
553  return value;
554  }
555 
556 }; // class ArrayImpl
